14. ROADMAP
This roadmap defines the strategic evolution of the product from MVP → v1 → v1.5 → v2 → long‑term vision.
It balances:

Speed

Safety

Emotional UX

AI intelligence

Multi‑provider expansion

Monetization

Platform growth

The roadmap is sequenced, realistic, and aligned with user psychology.

14.1 Roadmap Overview
The product evolves in five phases:

MVP — Core Swipe Experience (Gmail only)

v1 — Multi‑Provider + Emotional UX

v1.5 — Automation + AI Intelligence

v2 — Multi‑Inbox OS + Deep Insights

Long‑Term — The Universal Inbox Layer

Each phase is detailed below.

14.2 MVP (0.1 → 1.0)
Timeline: 6–10 weeks
Goal: Ship the fastest, safest, most satisfying inbox cleanup experience.

Included
Gmail integration

Swipe engine

Undo system

Newsletter detection

Basic AI suggestions

Onboarding + trust

Mini victory screen

Progress bar

Basic insights

Domain nuke (with confirmation)

Logging + database

Not Included
Multi‑provider

Automation

Advanced AI

Gamification

Boss fights

Zen/Rage modes

Success Criteria
Users clear 50 emails in < 2 minutes

Day‑1 retention > 40%

Gmail connection rate > 70%

First swipe < 30 seconds

14.3 v1 — Multi‑Provider + Emotional UX
Timeline: 1–2 months after MVP
Goal: Expand reach + deepen emotional experience.

Included
Outlook integration

Yahoo integration

iCloud integration

Fastmail integration

IMAP fallback

Combo system

Sound packs

Haptic variations

Streaks

Themed UI (garden/dojo)

Improved victory screen

Why this matters
Expands TAM

Increases retention

Strengthens emotional connection

Makes the product feel alive

Success Criteria
Multi‑provider support > 90% of users

Session length increases

Streak adoption > 50%

14.4 v1.5 — Automation + AI Intelligence
Timeline: 1–2 months after v1
Goal: Turn the product into a self‑maintaining inbox system.

Included
Auto‑delete rules

Auto‑block rules

Auto‑archive rules

Auto‑keep rules

AI rule suggestions

Persistent offender detection

Domain rotation detection

Sender clustering

Inbox health score

Weekly insights

Why this matters
Reduces daily effort

Builds long‑term retention

Creates “set it and forget it” value

Moves product from tool → system

Success Criteria
Automation adoption > 30%

Inbox volume reduction > 60%

Weekly return rate increases

14.5 v2 — Multi‑Inbox OS + Deep Insights
Timeline: 2–4 months after v1.5
Goal: Become the central control layer for all inboxes.

Included
Unified inbox view

Cross‑provider rules

Multi‑account cleanup

AI‑powered inbox summaries

AI‑powered sender analysis

Time‑saved analytics

Domain intelligence

Behavioral insights

Inbox optimization recommendations

Why this matters
Moves product into “Inbox OS” territory

Creates defensibility

Enables enterprise use cases

Unlocks premium monetization

Success Criteria
Multi‑account adoption > 40%

Weekly insights engagement > 50%

Inbox health score becomes a core metric

14.6 Long‑Term Vision — The Universal Inbox Layer
Timeline: 6–18 months
Goal: Become the universal intelligence layer on top of all email providers.

Included
AI Inbox Assistant

“Explain my inbox”

“Summarize my week”

“Predict future clutter”

“Optimize my email habits”

Cross‑platform integrations

Slack

Teams

SMS

WhatsApp

Calendar

Marketplace for:

Sender reputation

Domain intelligence

Cleanup packs

Automation templates

Enterprise version

Team cleanup

Shared rules

Compliance mode

Why this matters
Creates a category‑defining product

Builds a moat

Expands into B2B

Turns the product into infrastructure

Success Criteria
Enterprise adoption

Marketplace revenue

AI assistant usage

Inbox OS becomes the default layer

14.7 Strategic Principles
1. Emotion first
Every release must increase emotional satisfaction.

2. Safety always
Undo everywhere.
No irreversible actions.
No content reading.

3. AI as assistant, not agent
AI suggests.
User decides.

4. Build trust before automation
Automation comes only after user confidence.

5. Ship fast, iterate faster
Small releases.
Continuous improvement.

14.8 Roadmap Summary Table
Phase	Focus	Key Features
MVP	Core experience	Swipe engine, Gmail, Undo, Basic AI
v1	Emotional UX + Providers	Outlook/Yahoo/iCloud, combos, streaks
v1.5	Automation + AI	Auto‑rules, clustering, insights
v2	Inbox OS	Multi‑inbox, deep analytics, AI summaries
Long‑Term	Universal layer	AI assistant, marketplace, enterprise
